	<section type="slide" position="3" xmlns="">
		<title>Multi-Line Comments</title>
		<content>Multi-Line Comments Java also supports comments that span multiple lines. You start this type of comment with a forward slash followed by an asterisk, and end it with an asterisk followed by a forward slash.  For example: /*  This is also a     comment spanning     multiple lines */ Note that Java does not support nested multi-line comments.  However, you can nest single-line comments within multi-line comments. /* This is a single-line comment:     // a single-line comment  */ Multi-Line Comments Java also supports comments that span multiple lines. You start this type of comment with a forward slash followed by an asterisk, and end it with an asterisk followed by a forward slash.  For example: /*  This is also a     comment spanning     multiple lines */ Note that Java does not support nested multi-line comments.  However, you can nest single-line comments within multi-line comments. /* This is a single-line comment:     // a single-line comment  */ </content>
