	</section>
	<section type="slide" position="6" xmlns="">
		<title></title>
		<content>When a documentation comment begins with more than two asterisks, Javadoc assumes that you want to create a &amp;quot;box&amp;quot; around the comment in the source code. It simply ignores the extra asterisks. /********************** This is the start of a method ***********************/ This will retain just the text &amp;quot;This is the start of a method&amp;quot; for the documentation. When a documentation comment begins with more than two asterisks, Javadoc assumes that you want to create a &amp;quot;box&amp;quot; around the comment in the source code. It simply ignores the extra asterisks. /********************** This is the start of a method ***********************/ This will retain just the text &amp;quot;This is the start of a method&amp;quot; for the documentation. </content>
